CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Developmental Disabilities Administration – Self–Directed Services – Parent
3 Providers
4 FOR the purpose of clarifying that a parent of the recipient may provide services for the
5 recipient of self–directed services under certain circumstances; altering the
6 circumstances under which a family member or legal guardian may provide services
7 for the recipient of self–directed services; and generally relating to the
8 Developmental Disabilities Administration self–directed services.
9 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
10 Article – Health – General
11 Section 7–409(a)(4)
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – Health – General
17 7–409.
