2 HOUSE BILL 1053
1 (a) The Administration shall provide to a recipient who receives self–directed
2 services:
3 (4) An option for a PARENT, ANOTHER family member, or A legal guardian
4 of the recipient to provide services for the recipient, if:
5 (i) The recipient or an individual authorized to make care decisions
6 on behalf of the recipient chooses the PARENT, family member, OR LEGAL GUARDIAN to
7 provide the services; and
8 (ii) The recipient also hires a support broker; AND
9 (III) THE SERVICES ARE AUTHORIZED TO BE PROVIDED BY THE
10 PARENT, ANOTHER FAMILY MEMBER, OR THE LEGAL GUARDIAN OF THE RECIPIENT
11 BY AN ADMINISTRATION WAIVER APPROVED BY THE CENTERS FOR MEDICARE AND
12 MEDICAID SERVICES;
13 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
14 October 1, 2025.
